The paper involves the use of deep learning techniques for image classification and diagnosis, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of patient information and medical imaging for diagnosis also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper specifically deals with medical imaging of cervical tissue, which falls under the medical imaging (cs.Medical Imaging) sub-category. Finally, the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for feature extraction and classification indicates the involvement of deep learning (cs.DL) sub-category.
